citations:
    citation-affc-cersei-vii:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Cersei VII"
            text_from_source: "Cersei visits Margaery in her tower cell in the Great Sept of Baelor, where she is imprisoned by the Faith."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Cersei visits Margaery Tyrell confined in the Great Sept. She informs Margaery that a trial by the Faith (seven judges) is likely, and manipulates Margaery by making trial by combat sound impossible (only weak Kingsguard available). Then Cersei goes to see the High Sparrow, and discovers Osney Kettleblack has been tortured into recanting — he now confesses that it was Cersei who sent him to murder the previous High Septon. Cersei flees but is seized by the Faith and imprisoned in a tower cell, stripped naked, accused of adultery, regicide, and treason."
